headlines.description: — On their third try, the Cavaliers didn't collapse against the Bucks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 36, leads Cavs past Giannis, Bucks 114-106

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 22 points and 10 rebounds and the Philadelphia 76ers used a balanced scoring attack to extend their winning streak to six games with a 113-93 win over the Detroit Pistons on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid leads balanced attack, 76ers beat Pistons, 113-93

headlines.description: — Ayo Dosunmu banked in a putback jumper as time expired and the Chicago Bulls rallied after blowing an 18-point lead to win their second straight game, 110-108 over the Atlanta Hawks on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Ayo Dosunmu beats buzzer, Bulls beat Hawks 110-108

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored 33 points and the Indiana Pacers opened a 30-point lead in the first half before holding off the slumping Boston Celtics 117-112 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton scores 33 points, Pacers beat slumping Celtics

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Jacque Vaughn wasn't aware his Brooklyn Nets had the best first half in their history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets score 91 in 1st half, wallop weary Warriors 143-113

events.name: Toronto Raptors at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored a career-high 52 points and the Toronto Raptors snapped the New York Knicks’ NBA-leading eight-game winning streak 113-106 Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks' NBA-leading 8-game win streak ends versus Raptors

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 25 points, rookie Paolo Banchero had 23 points and 13 rebounds, and the Orlando Magic overcame a 15-point second-half deficit to beat the Houston Rockets 116-110 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic rally past Rockets 116-110 for 7th win in 8 games

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 25 points, 10 assists and nine rebounds and Dallas Mavericks beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 104-99 on Wednesday night to split the two-game set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavericks rebound to beat Timberwolves for split

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 27 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder defeated the Portland Trail Blazers for the second time in three days, 101-98 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 27 as Thunder top Portland again

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 13 points, 21 rebounds and 12 assists to lead the Sacramento Kings to a 134-120 win over the Los Angeles Lakers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis leads balanced scoring as Kings beat Lakers 134-120

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 22 points, Nicolas Batum added 21 and the injury-ravaged Los Angeles Clippers had their whole roster available in a 126-105 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers use full roster to rout Hornets 126-105
